reporter_caption.center: PARES v. CITY OF CINCINNATI, 126 Ohio St. 380 (1933)

syllabus.italic: Supreme Court — Dismissals — No debatable constitutional

opinion.posture: ERROR to the Court of Appeals of Hamilton county.
opinion.attorneys:
Messrs. Strother, Greenberg Schubert, for plaintiff in error.
Mr. John D. Ellis, city solicitor, and Mr. Francis T.Bartlett, for defendant in error.
opinion.opinion_text:
It is ordered and adjudged that said petition in error be, and the same hereby is, dismissed for the reason no debatable constitutional question is involved in said cause.
Petition in error dismissed.
WEYGANDT, C.J., DAY, ALLEN, STEPHENSON, JONES, and MATTHIAS, JJ., concur.
KINKADE, J., not participating.Page 381
